{{ Infobox Officeholder | name =Ottavio Ragni | image=ITA-Ragni.jpg | imagesize= | caption= |order1= [[List of colonial governors of Italian Tripolitania|Italian Governor of Tripolitana]] | term_start1=2 September 1912 |term_end1 = 2 June 1913 | predecessor1=[[Carlo Caneva]] | successor1=[[Vincenzo Garioni]] | birth_date= 21 April 1852 |birth_place = [[Romagnano Sesia]] | death_date= {{Death date and age|1919|5|21|1852|4|21}} | death_place= Romagnano Sesia | nationality= |party = | footnotes= }} '''Ottavio Ragni''' was an Italian general. He had been the governor of [[Tripolitania]] between (1912-1913).
At the [[battle of Adwa]], during the [[First Italo-Ethiopian War|Italian invasion of Abyssinia]], he led the 3rd Infantry Regiment Africa.<ref>[http://www.geocities.ws/Athens/Styx/9891/aduit05.htm FORMAZIONE DI MARCIA DELLA 2^ BRIGATA DI FANTERIA VERSO ADUA]</ref>
At the beginning of [[World War I]] he commanded the 1st corps of the [[Fourth Army (Italy)|4th Italian army]].<ref>[https://books.google.com.ly/books?id=xO4xN7PmusUC&printsec=frontcover&hl=ar#v=onepage&q&f=false The Beginning of Futility Gaetano V. Cavallaro]</ref>
